00:26:48,191 --> 00:26:50,819
is learning to take time out
to help Team Flash grow, too.

489
00:26:51,694 --> 00:26:54,173
I've learned just as much from them
as they've learned from me.

490
00:26:54,197 --> 00:26:56,407
It's like being a CSI.
Every day I work with

491
00:26:56,825 --> 00:26:58,701
all my fellow officers
in all departments.

492
00:27:01,913 --> 00:27:05,750
I mean... I do miss
scientific collaboration.

493
00:27:07,043 --> 00:27:09,963
It's like I told Chester,
I'm not a Legend anymore.

494
00:27:10,421 --> 00:27:12,757
And I don't have the C.C.P.D.

495
00:27:13,550 --> 00:27:14,550
So what?

496
00:27:15,218 --> 00:27:17,846
You're Ray Palmer, Legacy Honoree.

497
00:27:18,596 --> 00:27:21,558
If you want something
that doesn't exist, invent it.

498
00:27:39,617 --> 00:27:42,412
This copy is damn well-written.

499
00:27:43,288 --> 00:27:45,999
What exactly are you looking for?

500
00:27:46,082 --> 00:27:47,417
If you even know.

501
00:27:48,251 --> 00:27:50,587
Look, these stories aren't bad.

502
00:27:51,129 --> 00:27:53,131
They're well sourced. Thorough.

503
00:27:53,214 --> 00:27:57,886
But, CCC Media is about more
than just providing facts.

504
00:27:58,761 --> 00:28:00,513
It's the voice of the people,

505
00:28:00,847 --> 00:28:03,683
which means
it needs to have something to say.

506
00:28:03,892 --> 00:28:06,227
It's literally the opposite
of objective journalism.

507
00:28:06,811 --> 00:28:08,688
How about we leave
the editorializing to Iris?

508
00:28:09,731 --> 00:28:13,484
Okay, it's right there in the name.
<i>Central City Citizen.</i>

509
00:28:14,986 --> 00:28:17,822
Yeah, you guys landed
some pretty major interviews,

510
00:28:18,114 --> 00:28:21,743
but every person's voice
in this city deserves to be heard.

511
00:28:21,826 --> 00:28:24,245
Not just the most famous
or high-profile ones.

512
00:28:24,329 --> 00:28:27,790
So what, we're not even supposed to talk
to the DA or the mayor anymore?

513
00:28:27,916 --> 00:28:29,125
Yes, talk to them.

514
00:28:29,584 --> 00:28:32,670
But then go talk to the janitor
who cleans the mayor's office

515
00:28:33,254 --> 00:28:37,008
or a mom working two jobs
just to pay her bills.

516
00:28:37,217 --> 00:28:41,179
Because corruption in this city,
it affects them more than anyone.

517
00:28:42,972 --> 00:28:45,850
Don't you guys see?
When we're at our best,

518
00:28:46,184 --> 00:28:49,771
our readers see themselves
reflected in our stories.

519
00:28:52,690 --> 00:28:54,359
So, try again.

520
00:28:55,485 --> 00:28:58,988
But this time...
remember who you're writing for.

521
00:29:10,083 --> 00:29:12,043
You've already
accomplished so much...

522
00:29:12,377 --> 00:29:14,629
...and now you're a CCTC Legacy Honoree.

523
00:29:16,047 --> 00:29:18,132
What's next for you? Retirement?

524
00:29:19,050 --> 00:29:20,718
Uh...

525
00:29:21,761 --> 00:29:24,305
Well, honestly I...

526
00:29:27,475 --> 00:29:28,476
I'm not sure.

527
00:29:30,228 --> 00:29:32,105
That question's come up
for me a lot today.

528
00:29:32,522 --> 00:29:35,149
And, you know, I have been doing
a ton of research lately,

529
00:29:35,233 --> 00:29:39,070
but, I also don't want to repeat
my previous achievements.

530
00:29:39,404 --> 00:29:42,657
So, I guess I'm having
conflicting thoughts about it.

531
00:29:43,408 --> 00:29:44,701
It's a tough decision.

532
00:29:47,036 --> 00:29:48,079
So, you know what?

533
00:29:48,871 --> 00:29:51,040
Maybe we should all find out together...

534
00:29:52,166 --> 00:29:53,166
next year.

535
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,466
Okay, and on that note,

536
00:30:00,550 --> 00:30:02,468
let's thank Ray Palmer
for joining us today.

537
00:30:12,186 --> 00:30:13,354
You all should run.

538
00:30:18,776 --> 00:30:20,403
<i>While you still can.</i>

539
00:30:22,530 --> 00:30:23,530
Everybody go.

540
00:30:24,157 --> 00:30:25,115
Go!

541
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:30,620
Flash,

542
00:30:31,164 --> 00:30:32,582
don't make this difficult.

543
00:30:34,167 --> 00:30:35,335
Show yourself.

544
00:30:38,588 --> 00:30:39,964
I'm not gonna let you hurt anyone.

545
00:30:41,090 --> 00:30:42,930
Why don't you just tell me
what it is you want?

546
00:30:43,176 --> 00:30:44,177
Of course.

547
00:30:45,261 --> 00:30:47,513
I came a long way to find you, Flash.

548
00:30:48,431 --> 00:30:49,682
And now that I have,

549
00:30:52,268 --> 00:30:53,478
I'm going to kill you.

550
00:31:00,693 --> 00:31:03,613
Whoever you are,
if you're looking for a fight,

551
00:31:04,364 --> 00:31:05,364
you found one.

552
00:31:08,743 --> 00:31:09,786
Oh, snap!

553
00:31:10,078 --> 00:31:11,704
Time for Flash to do what he does best

554
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,080
and kick some butt.

555
00:31:13,790 --> 00:31:15,458
You're nothing like I expected.

556
00:31:16,751 --> 00:31:17,919
Not that it matters.

557
00:31:18,628 --> 00:31:20,254
Those who were once good

558
00:31:21,798 --> 00:31:23,174
die just as easily.

559
00:31:37,105 --> 00:31:39,190
- Oh, well, that's not good.
- What is that thing?

560
00:31:39,482 --> 00:31:41,859
Oh, I'm picking up some
seriously advanced tech readings.

561
00:31:42,026 --> 00:31:43,587
You just have that thing
in your back pocket?

562
00:31:43,611 --> 00:31:45,321
No, I just picked it up
from right there.

563
00:31:46,489 --> 00:31:48,074
Oh, yeah. Tech Con, right.

564
00:31:48,157 --> 00:31:49,797
I think Barry's gonna need
a helping hand.

565
00:31:49,951 --> 00:31:53,538
Wait. What?
Like a superhero team up with the Atom?

566
00:31:55,164 --> 00:31:56,164
What changed your mind?

567
00:31:59,293 --> 00:32:01,337
My friends. An old one and a new one.

568
00:32:01,921 --> 00:32:03,131
But I'm still not a Legend.

569
00:32:04,715 --> 00:32:06,092
Man, you're a hell of a lot more.

570
00:32:28,322 --> 00:32:30,408
I was born amongst the stars, Flash.

571
00:32:30,491 --> 00:32:32,618
Trapping me in a vacuum was pointless.

572
00:32:33,286 --> 00:32:36,831
Now surrender...
and I promise you won't suffer.

573
00:32:40,585 --> 00:32:41,794
And the suit still fits.

574
00:32:42,628 --> 00:32:45,423
- Hey! You been working out?
- Yeah, thank you for noticing.

575
00:32:47,633 --> 00:32:48,968
- All right, you ready?
- Yeah.

576
00:32:53,723 --> 00:32:55,850
Flash! Atom! Who are you firing at?

577
00:32:56,100 --> 00:32:57,518
Yeah, yeah. He's right behind you.

578
00:33:09,489 --> 00:33:11,032
Oh, now I know how Diggle feels.

579
00:33:11,782 --> 00:33:14,452
This guy isn't just strong.
I think he's messing with our minds.

580
00:33:14,952 --> 00:33:15,952
<i>Correct.</i>

581
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:19,582
<i>This isn't your fight, Atom.
Now leave while you still can.</i>

582
00:33:19,665 --> 00:33:20,708
Everyone has a weakness.

583
00:33:22,043 --> 00:33:23,252
I'll keep him occupied.

584
00:33:42,438 --> 00:33:45,608
You can't fool me
with a speed mirage, Flash.

585
00:33:46,192 --> 00:33:48,110
My mind is too powerful.

586
00:33:48,236 --> 00:33:50,154
Wait, you said I was good once.

587
00:33:51,572 --> 00:33:54,033
What happened to me? You owe me that.

588
00:33:55,284 --> 00:33:56,410
As you wish.

589
00:34:01,874 --> 00:34:04,752
<i>Bear witness to a coming Armageddon</i>

590
00:34:04,919 --> 00:34:07,046
<i>that you create ten years from now.</i>

591
00:34:08,089 --> 00:34:10,591
<i>One that destroys your own planet.</i>

592
00:34:12,593 --> 00:34:14,178
It's already happened, Flash.

593
00:34:14,262 --> 00:34:16,681
That's why I, Despero, have to kill you.

594
00:34:18,307 --> 00:34:20,142
It's how I save our world.

595
00:34:33,531 --> 00:34:35,324
No!

596
00:34:37,285 --> 00:34:39,245
- Man, whatever you did...
- Any time, Flash.

597
00:34:39,537 --> 00:34:40,621
- Hey!
- Hey, you guys okay?

598
00:34:41,038 --> 00:34:42,038
Yeah.

599
00:34:42,123 --> 00:34:43,207
Where'd that thing go?

600
00:34:43,874 --> 00:34:45,209
I don't know.

601
00:34:53,801 --> 00:34:56,929
Barry, you know you're not destined
to destroy the world, right?

602
00:34:57,013 --> 00:35:00,516
Yeah, I know. But the visions Despero
showed me seemed so real.

603
00:35:00,975 --> 00:35:02,310
And he said "our world."

604
00:35:02,602 --> 00:35:04,020
But what does that even mean?

605
00:35:04,103 --> 00:35:05,771
I don't know... yet.

606
00:35:06,105 --> 00:35:07,356
What if he's mind-punking you?

607
00:35:07,732 --> 00:35:10,568
Like how he made you and Ray
see an illusion during your fight?

608
00:35:11,861 --> 00:35:12,903
I don't think he was.

609
00:35:13,446 --> 00:35:15,072
Every test I've run on Barry shows that

610
00:35:15,156 --> 00:35:17,408
he's completely fine,
mentally and physically.

611
00:35:17,575 --> 00:35:20,286
Well, I scanned the residual feelings
that Despero left behind

612
00:35:20,369 --> 00:35:23,539
inside your mind,
and there was no doubt.

613
00:35:24,081 --> 00:35:26,876
Despero was telling the truth.
He really did see those things.

614
00:35:26,959 --> 00:35:28,628
Which means everyone's in danger.

615
00:35:28,711 --> 00:35:31,839
No, no. There's no way that you're
the bad guy in this situation.

616
00:35:31,922 --> 00:35:34,425
What we need to do right now
is find out the truth.

617
00:35:34,508 --> 00:35:36,552
I have a bad feeling it's gonna find us.

618
00:35:36,636 --> 00:35:39,430
Once Despero gets back
from wherever Ray sent him.

619
00:35:39,513 --> 00:35:43,476
Yeah. Well, the tech inside
his belt was so complex,

620
00:35:43,809 --> 00:35:45,853
I could barely recognize
the navigation system.

621
00:35:45,936 --> 00:35:49,398
So, instead of sending him to a specific
location, I tried a random setting.

622
00:35:49,982 --> 00:35:51,233
Who knows where he went.

623
00:35:51,567 --> 00:35:53,319
- Or when he's coming back.
- Barr...

624
00:35:53,778 --> 00:35:56,447
how do we beat
a ten-foot-tall red alien,

625
00:35:56,530 --> 00:35:59,325
who thinks like Grodd
and punches like Fuerza?

626
00:35:59,992 --> 00:36:02,161
By figuring out
what kind of alien he is.

627
00:36:02,453 --> 00:36:05,373
Get that and you may have some idea
of what his weaknesses are.

628
00:36:05,498 --> 00:36:07,667
- Like Kryptonians.
- And Kryptonite.

629
00:36:08,250 --> 00:36:10,044
Great idea. I'll call Alex
in National City.

630
00:36:10,127 --> 00:36:11,253
Yeah. So what do we do?

631
00:36:11,504 --> 00:36:13,756
Well, he took our best shots
like they were nothing.

632
00:36:13,839 --> 00:36:15,841
- We need to be ready.
- For what?

633
00:36:16,967 --> 00:36:17,968
The fight of our lives.

634
00:36:23,057 --> 00:36:24,057
Iris.

635
00:36:24,517 --> 00:36:27,144
This account of Despero
fighting Flash and Atom,

636
00:36:27,645 --> 00:36:28,645
it's amazing.

637
00:36:29,063 --> 00:36:30,063
Is Barry okay?

638
00:36:30,564 --> 00:36:34,568
Yeah, it's just Despero is like
no one we've ever faced before.

639
00:36:35,695 --> 00:36:36,695
Any notes?

640
00:36:37,029 --> 00:36:38,739
Just one. Publish this.

641
00:36:39,156 --> 00:36:41,200
Now. People need to read it.

642
00:36:41,742 --> 00:36:44,620
You saw everything and survived.
The city needs to know it can, too.

643
00:36:45,955 --> 00:36:48,332
By the way, I read the revised articles

644
00:36:48,416 --> 00:36:50,418
that you had Vanya, Aariz
and Taylor write.

645
00:36:51,043 --> 00:36:52,043
And?

646
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,296
We're going straight to print
with all of them.

647
00:36:55,965 --> 00:36:57,901
Whatever you did to inspire
quality work like this,

648
00:36:57,925 --> 00:36:59,343
it must have gotten through.

649
00:36:59,719 --> 00:37:00,719
Thank God.

650
00:37:01,512 --> 00:37:04,181
But they're still not happy with me.

651
00:37:04,557 --> 00:37:06,225
Mm. Welcome to management.

652
00:37:10,771 --> 00:37:12,940
Are you sure you don't
need me to stick around?

653
00:37:13,065 --> 00:37:15,419
Nora can handle any
supernatural emergencies while I'm gone,

654
00:37:15,443 --> 00:37:17,611
and like you said, Despero
could come back any minute.

655
00:37:17,737 --> 00:37:20,906
It's okay. We're on it,
and if Despero comes back again...

656
00:37:21,115 --> 00:37:23,200
The Atom will embiggen, yeah?

657
00:37:23,951 --> 00:37:25,870
No? All right. Keep working on that one.

658
00:37:27,246 --> 00:37:29,457
Chester, what you did
back there at Jitters...

659
00:37:29,540 --> 00:37:32,376
- Was a huge mistake, I know...
- Was the best gift possible.

660
00:37:33,210 --> 00:37:35,254
Between that and helping Barry
again as the Atom,

661
00:37:35,337 --> 00:37:37,548
I have now realized
that there's a middle ground

662
00:37:37,631 --> 00:37:41,135
to this whole balance thing.
Which is why I want to return the favor.

663
00:37:41,343 --> 00:37:44,346
So, what if I created
a non-profit organization

664
00:37:44,430 --> 00:37:46,932
to fund young scientists
like your Jitters friends?

665
00:37:49,059 --> 00:37:50,811
- That would be awesome.
- Great!

666
00:37:50,978 --> 00:37:53,564
I was thinking I could call it
the Quincy P. Runk Foundation,

667
00:37:53,856 --> 00:37:56,066
if that's okay?
Barry told me about your father.

668
00:38:01,238 --> 00:38:02,238
Oh!

669
00:38:06,035 --> 00:38:09,830
Uh... Yeah. If you ever need, like,
a consultant or anything like that.

670
00:38:09,914 --> 00:38:10,914
I know who to call.

671
00:38:14,251 --> 00:38:15,252
Oh, and, Barry...

672
00:38:16,587 --> 00:38:19,587
There's one sure way to prove to Despero
that you'd never destroy the world.

673
00:38:19,757 --> 00:38:20,757
What's that?

674
00:38:21,675 --> 00:38:22,995
Just show him who you really are.

675
00:38:23,844 --> 00:38:25,644
Like you do with this team
each and every day.

676
00:38:37,900 --> 00:38:39,944
Barry, we got an alien signal
coming in hot.

677
00:38:41,153 --> 00:38:42,488
Barry, are you sure about this?

678
00:38:43,072 --> 00:38:44,240
Yeah, it's like Ray said,

679
00:38:45,241 --> 00:38:47,135
the only way to convince Despero
I'm not a threat,

680
00:38:47,159 --> 00:38:48,536
is to show him who I really am.

681
00:38:52,373 --> 00:38:54,333
Prepare to die, Flash.

682
00:38:54,917 --> 00:38:56,460
Every life ends sooner or later.

683
00:38:57,169 --> 00:38:59,046
Wise words from a dead man.

684
00:38:59,296 --> 00:39:00,816
Despero, I'm not going to
fight you again.

685
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:02,883
Really? I'm disappointed.

686
00:39:03,467 --> 00:39:05,719
Striking down a defenseless foe?

687
00:39:06,554 --> 00:39:08,347
Well, there's no pleasure in that.

688
00:39:08,430 --> 00:39:09,557
So you enjoy killing?

689
00:39:12,685 --> 00:39:15,479
Twist my words at your own risk!

690
00:39:16,647 --> 00:39:17,773
You wanted to kill me.

691
00:39:18,732 --> 00:39:19,859
I'm not running anywhere.

692
00:39:25,990 --> 00:39:26,991
Neither am I.

693
00:39:28,951 --> 00:39:31,036
In another time, on another world,

694
00:39:31,745 --> 00:39:33,998
we could've fought side by side,
you and I.

695
00:39:35,541 --> 00:39:37,293
There's great strength in you, Flash.

696
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:39,503
But I've seen your future.

697
00:39:41,005 --> 00:39:43,883
The lives you take,
the betrayals you revel in.

698
00:39:44,842 --> 00:39:46,886
You're the most dangerous kind of killer

699
00:39:48,012 --> 00:39:50,139
because you hide in the body of a hero.

700
00:39:50,222 --> 00:39:51,265
I'm not a killer.

701
00:39:53,142 --> 00:39:55,686
I'm not whatever you think I am.
I can prove it.

702
00:39:55,853 --> 00:39:59,273
If you let me show you the truth.
Or are you gonna take an innocent life

703
00:39:59,940 --> 00:40:01,025
just to prove you're right?

704
00:40:01,942 --> 00:40:04,403
You're either very stupid or very brave.

705
00:40:05,946 --> 00:40:07,448
I can't decide which.

706
00:40:07,573 --> 00:40:09,366
Find out. Scan my mind.

707
00:40:10,159 --> 00:40:11,619
See for yourself, then decide.

708
00:40:18,542 --> 00:40:20,502
I see no deception in your mind.

709
00:40:22,755 --> 00:40:27,635
But I do see truth... and honor.

710
00:40:31,013 --> 00:40:34,391
Flash, you're asking me
to risk allowing the future

711
00:40:34,475 --> 00:40:36,268
I've already witnessed, to unfold.

712
00:40:38,437 --> 00:40:39,438
I'm sorry.

713
00:40:41,398 --> 00:40:42,900
There's too many lives at stake.

714
00:40:43,692 --> 00:40:46,320
Don't you see? This is why I came back.

715
00:40:47,071 --> 00:40:49,990
This is the purpose
that I swore to uphold.

716
00:40:50,491 --> 00:40:51,700
What if you're wrong about me?

717
00:40:54,244 --> 00:40:58,040
I've spent my entire life
protecting this world.

718
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:02,103
All I'm asking for is a chance to prove
I'd never turn my back on it.

719
00:41:02,127 --> 00:41:04,129
Why should I believe you?

720
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:11,000
Because my name is Barry Allen.

721
00:41:12,221 --> 00:41:13,389
And I have nothing to hide.

722
00:41:16,016 --> 00:41:18,227
Your boldness impresses me, Flash.

723
00:41:20,270 --> 00:41:22,314
And has earned you a stay of execution.

724
00:41:24,191 --> 00:41:27,277
You now have seven Earth days to prove
that you won't become the monster

725
00:41:27,361 --> 00:41:29,196
I've already witnessed in the future.

726
00:41:29,530 --> 00:41:31,991
If you can't convince me in that time

727
00:41:32,116 --> 00:41:35,202
or if I find any trace
of a darker nature,

728
00:41:36,495 --> 00:41:38,330
I will end your existence.

